“law”  means  any  written  law  relating  to  a  matter  with  respect 
to  which  Parliament  has  power  to  make  laws,  but,  except  in 
sections  14,  15  and  16,  does  not  include  this Act;

(a)  any  repealing  enactment  and  any  table  or  list  of 
repealed  enactments,  whether  contained  in  a 
schedule  or  otherwise;

(vi)  to add a long title or a short title to any law which may 
require it, and to alter the long title or short title of any 
law;

Provided  that  such  tables  of  contents,  chronological 
tables,  references  and  notes  shall  not  form  any  part  of 
the  law  in  which  they  appear;

(xv)  to correct grammatical, typographical and similar mistakes 
and for that purpose to make verbal additions, omissions, 
or  alterations  not  affecting  the  meaning  of  any  law;

(ii)  a list of the laws by which the law has been amended up 
to  the  date  of  its  revision  showing  the  dates  on  which 
the  amendments  came  into  force;
